{"title_page": "Khariar", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2018}}\n{{more citations needed|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Khariar\n| other_name                      = Raja-Khadial, Raja Khariar\n| settlement_type                 = small town \n| image_skyline                   = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|20.28|N|82.77|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[Tehsil|Sub division]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Odisha]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Nuapada district|Nuapada]]\n| subdivision_name3               = [[Tehsil|Khariar]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date                = \n| founder                         = \n| named_for                       = \n| government_type                 = Local NAC\n| governing_body                  = NAC Khariar\n| leader_title                    = Chairman\n| leader_name                     = '''Balkrushna sabar'''\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = 16\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = 226\n| population_total                = 15,087\n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_rank                \n| population_demonym              = \n| demographics_type1              = Languages\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code                     = 766107\n| area_code                       = 06671\n| area_code_type                  = Telephone code\n| registration_plate              = OD-26\n| website                         = {{URL|odisha.gov.in}}\n| footnotes                       = \n| leader_title3                   = Member of the Legislative Assembly\n| leader_name3                    = '''Sir Aadhiraj Panigrahi'''\n| leader_title4                   = Member of Parliament\n| leader_name4                    = '''Basant panda''\n| demographics1_info1             = [[odia language|odia]] and [[English language|English]]\n}}\n\n'''Khariar''' (also called '''Khadial''' , '''Kharhial''' or '''Raj khariar''' ) is a town and a [[nagar panchayat|notified area committee]] in [[Nuapada district]] of the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Odisha]].\n\n==Economy==\n[[Nuapada district]] in the State of [[Odisha]] is in the western part of odisha in India and Khariar is located in the heart of [[Nuapada district]]. It comes under a [[rain shadow]] belt .\nKhariar is the one of the major towns in Nuapada district. It is the main business centre in the locality. It has a daily market and a weekly baazar takes place every Friday. Most people of Khariar are middle-class, which includes government employees, small shopkeepers, businessmen etc.\n[[File:Khariar street.jpg|thumb|Khariar street]] [[File:Khariar market.jpg|thumb|Khariar market]]\n\n==Geography==\nKhariar is located at {{coord|20.28|N|82.77|E|}}.<ref>[http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/21/Kharhial.html Falling Rain Genomics, Inc - Khariar]</ref> It has an average elevation of {{convert|226|m|ft|abbr=on}}. It is located in the Western part of Odisha, close to the border of Raipur District Chhattisgarh State. It belongs to the Mahanadi basin the Eastern Ghats where mountains are interspersed with wide valleys. The elevation is about 200 meters. The climate is tropical with the rainfall is due to the South West [[monsoon]], There are few government and private schools and colleges in the region. Odia is the official language of the people. Furthermore, the region is well connected with roads to many town and also railways to other part of the state. The nearest airport located is [[Raipur]] in [[Chhattisgarh]] and nearest railway station located at [[Kantabanjhi]] which is 35KM Away from Khariar. <ref>[http://www.indiamapped.com/orissa/nuapada/khariar/. Indian Regional Mapping]</ref>.\n\n==Demographics==\n\n{{As of|2011}} India [[census]] Khariar had a population of 15,087. Males constitute 51% of the population and females 49%. Khariar has an average literacy rate of 62%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 72%, and female literacy is 52%. In Khariar, 13% of the population is under 6 years of age.\n[[File:Khariar mahotsav.jpg|thumb|Khariar mahotsav]]\n\n==Areas==\n# Raja Pada\n# Nina Pada\n# Lalsaheb Pada\n# Dhuba Pada\n# Pattnaik Pada\n# Sahu Pada\n# Pathan Pada\n# Ada Pada\n# Annapurna Pada\n# Bangti Pada\n# Braman Pada\n# Sabar Pada\n# Putu Pada\n# Gousala Pada\n# Chelia Pada\n# Police Pada\n# Satnami Pada\n# Phokat Pada\n# Bijepur Pada\n# Chatria Pada\n# Parua Pada\n# Muktapur\n# Santi Nagar\n# Meher colony\n# Laxmi Nagar\n# Indra Nagar\n# Maruti Nagar\n# Sri Krushna Nagar\n# SriRam Nagar\n# Satyabadi Nagar\n# Vidya nagar\n# Padmasri Nagar\n# Gadramunda Pada\n# Padampur Pada\n# Badi\n# Chalanpada\n# Luhurapali\n# Kotipadar\n# irrigation colony\n# Dal pada\n# Mili Pada\nCity area of KHARIAR includes nearby sub-urban areas like Padmapur, Badi, Junani, Chindaguda, Chalanpada,kotipadar,chanabeda,bhaludungari,bhojpur\n\n==Education==\nKhariar has one of the highest school densities in Nuapada District. The best Odia Medium school is Saraswati sishu vidya mandir.\n\n===General colleges===\n* Khariar Autonomous College, Khariar\n* Model Degree College, Khariar\n* K.M. Degree College, Tukula\n* Women's Degree College, Khariar\n* Lokadrusti +3 Science College, Khariar\n\n===Higher secondary schools===\n* Khariar Higher Secondary School, Khariar\n* Khadial Mahila Higher Secondary School, Khariar\n* Government Vocational Higher Secondary School, Khariar\n* Mahatma Gandhi Science Higher Secondary School, Khariar\n* Parikshita Tiger Science Higher Secondary School, Khariar\n* Upendra Prabhakar Higher Secondary School, Tukla\n* Bibekananda Meher Higher Secondary School, Bhuliasikuan\n\n===Schools===\n\n* Raja A. T. High School, Khariar\n* SARASWATI SISHU VIDYA MANDIR, KHARIAR\n* Kendriya Vidyalaya, Khariar\n* Odisha Adarsha Vidyalaya, Badi, Khariar\n* Panchayat High School, Lohorapali\n* Govt. Girls' High School, Khariar\n* Khariar Public School\n* Chindaguda High School\n* Arabinda School\n* Shastri School\n* Imperial English Medium School\n* Little Star Play School\n* Mission Primary School\n* Taj Urudu Prathamika Vidyalaya\n* Balaka School\n* Balika School\n* Utkalabandhu School\n* Manikya devi School\n* BIJEPUR BLIND SCHOOL\n* BIJEPUR Govt primary school\n* Regional Conclusive High School, Khariar\n* St. Xaviers Public School, Lalsaheb Pada, Khariar\n* Jai Kishan Nodal High School, Bargaon\n* Western Odisha Residential Public School. Rajkhaiar\n*Duajhar High School, Duajhar\n\n===Technical colleges/institutions===\n* Government I.T.I. Khariar\n* Lokadrusti College of Advanced Technology\n* SRIIT Computer Education\n* KETAKI Academy\n* ASCMS Education\n\n==Medical facilities==\n* Evangelical Hospital, Khariar\n* Govt.Hospital, Khariar\n* District Headquarter Hospital, Nuapada\n\n==Transportation==\nKhariar is a major transportation hub in Nuapada District as people from the three blocks namely Boden, Sinapali and Khariar depend upon the mode of transportation available in Khariar. Though Khariar is not connected by rail, it is well connected by roads. The major roads passing through Khariar are NH 353, SH 16 etc. The nearest rail head is Kantabanji, which is situated 35&nbsp;km from Khariar. Another nearest railway station is Titlagarh (which is also the hottest place in India). The nearest airport is Raipur Airport situated 195&nbsp;km from Khariar.\n\n==Nearby towns==\n\n#[[Kantabanjhi]] 35&nbsp;km\n#[[Titlagarh]] 50&nbsp;km\n#[[Nuapada]] 70&nbsp;km\n#[[Balangir]] 112&nbsp;km\n#[[Bhawanipatna]] 70&nbsp;km\n#[[Raipur]] 190&nbsp;km\n#[[Khariar Road]] 78&nbsp;km\n#[[Sambalpur]] 240&nbsp;km\n#[[Bhubaneswar]] 430&nbsp;km\n#[[Kolkata]] 838&nbsp;km\n#[[Brahampur]] 338&nbsp;km\n\n==Religious places==\nThere are several religious places of different religion in Khariar, this indicates a diversity in religion, culture in Khariar. Some of the temples located in Khariar are:-\n\n* Maa Samaleswari Temple, near Azad Chowk\n* Raktambari mandir, near Azad Chowk\n* Hanuman Mandir, near Azad Chowk\n* Hanuman Mandir, Puruna Bustand\n* Dadhibamana Mandir, Badgudipada\n* Jagannath Temple\n* Ram Mandir\n* Hanuman Mandir, irrigation colony\n* Koshaleswar Temple, irrigation colony\n* Ganesh mandir, irrigation colony\n* Bhubaneswari mandir, irrigation colony\n* Shiva Temple, Duajhar\n* Maa Santoshi Mandir, Junen\n* Siva mandir, Tirbandh\n* Siva mandir, muktasagar\n* Gayatri Mandir, Chalanpada\n* Radhakrushna madir, Damapala\n* Shri Rameswara Siva Mandir, Bhaludungari\n* Shiv temple, dalpada\nSome of the other religious places of other communities are:\n* Mukti Marg Church, Khariar\n* Sunni Hanfi Jama Masjid, At-Masjid Pada, Khariar\n* Sunni Jamat Eidgah, NH-353 Near Khariar Autonomous College Khariar\n\n==Markets==\n* Khariar Daily Market \n* Goru Bazar (Weekly Market)\n* New Mraket\n\n==Tourist spots==\nThere are several tourist spots around Khariar. Some of them are listed below:-\n* Patalganga: Patalganga, a tourist spot located approximately 30&nbsp;km from Khariar is a beautiful tourist spot which attracts large numbers of pilgrims from different parts of nuapada district as well as from neighbouring districts. A temple of lord Shiva is also there.\n* [[Tikhali Dam, (Lower Indra Irrigation)|Tikhali dam]]: Tikhali dam, officially known as lower indra irrigation project is a dam located 17&nbsp;km apart from Khariar. It is an important picnic spot for the people of Khariar. Generally it gets crowded in new year occasion.\n* Rusipitha: Rusipitha is located near tukla (Linga Raj)\n*Jogimatha-Tukla\n\n==Culture==\nKhariar's culture is a blend of traditional festivals, food, dance etc. Khariar offers a cosmopolitan and diverse lifestyle with a variety of food, entertainment and standard of living. Khariar has a proud cultural heritage that arose due to intermingling of different religions. The major language used is Odia, which is widely used in each and every part of Khariar region. You can talk here in Hindi Too. English is widely used for official purpose. Nuakhai is the major festival celebrated in this region. The other festivals like rathayatra, dusshera, holi, dipawali, eid, Christmas, chindaguda (Dhanujatra Mahotsav, Anchalika Sanskrutik Utsav, (Chindaguda) are also celebrated in Khariar. Khariar organises Khariar Mahotsav<ref>{{cite web |title=Khariar Mahotsav 2019 |url=https://www.newstrend.news/204881/khariar-mahotsav-2019/ |website=newstrend.news |publisher=Newstrend}}</ref> every year, which attracts a large number of people from different places.\n\nKhariar is basically one of the peaceful town in Odisha . The town remains active from 8AM to 9:30PM usually. The activities of this town includes:- running of schools, shops or very small industries and bus communications. Other than these activities, political activities across the town is also common. In evenings it is a common sight to see youth playing at various fields (mostly at RAJA A.T. HIGH SCHOOL field, Vidya Mandir field, Bhojpur Field, College Field, and Shanti Nagar Field). In fact the veterans also participate in several fitness activities during evenings, like jogging near Canal Road, Padampur Road, Tukla Road, Nehena Road, or College Road.\n\n==Festivals==\n* Ratha Yatra (June\u2013July)\n* Khariar Mohatsav (Jan-Feb)\n* Kartik Purnima (Nov-Dec)\n* Diwali (November)\n* Holi (March)\n* Gurunanak Jayanti\n* Durga Puja\n* Ganesh puja\n* Biswakarma puja\n* Rakshya Bandhan\n* Ram Navami\n* Shivaratri\n* Holi\n* Independence day\n* Republic day\n* Gandhi jayanti\n* Janmastami\n* DhanuJatra\n* Ramzan & Eid\n* Bakareid\n* Moharram\n* Christmas (December)\n* Krushnalila\n* Eid Milad Un Nabi\n* NUAKHAI\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Nuapada district}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Nuapada district]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2018}}\n{{more citations needed|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Khariar\n| other_name                      = Raja-Khadial, Raja Khariar\n| settlement_type                 = small town \n| image_skyline                   = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|20.28|N|82.77|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[Tehsil|Sub division]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Odisha]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Nuapada district|Nuapada]]\n| subdivision_name3               = [[Tehsil|Khariar]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date                = \n| founder                         = \n| named_for                       = \n| government_type                 = Local NAC\n| governing_body                  = NAC Khariar\n| leader_title                    = Chairman\n| leader_name                     = '''Balkrushna sabar'''\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = 16\n| eleva